01:34:23.699 --> 01:34:24.867
I'm taking all of these with me.

1920
01:34:25.034 --> 01:34:27.370
I want all of these boxed up,
and I'm taking them.

1921
01:34:27.536 --> 01:34:28.663
You're trespassing!

1922
01:34:28.829 --> 01:34:30.039
It's not your patent!

1923
01:34:30.498 --> 01:34:32.375
These are my designs!

1924
01:34:33.709 --> 01:34:36.045
I'm not going anywhere without my molds.

1925
01:34:37.004 --> 01:34:38.547
What? No. No.

1926
01:34:38.714 --> 01:34:41.050
This is not stealing.
This is my property!

1927
01:34:41.217 --> 01:34:42.343
This is my property.

1928
01:34:42.510 --> 01:34:45.846
I have all of these designs.
These are all mine. They belong to me!

1929
01:34:46.013 --> 01:34:49.600
She's from out of state, John!
You've known me 15 years!

1930
01:34:49.767 --> 01:34:51.394
All right, come on, ma'am.
You're trespassing.

1931
01:34:51.560 --> 01:34:53.187
-What?
-Yeah. Come on.

1932
01:34:53.354 --> 01:34:54.730
-I'm not trespassing.
-Yeah, you're trespassing.

1933
01:34:54.897 --> 01:34:55.940
I was in his office.

1934
01:34:56.065 --> 01:34:57.400
-You don't know. Come on.
-He let me into his...

1935
01:34:57.566 --> 01:34:58.859
Gerhardt, you're not gonna
get away with this.

1936
01:34:58.901 --> 01:35:01.195
-You're not gonna get away with this!
-Be careful what you're saying.

1937
01:35:01.237 --> 01:35:02.279
You're a thief! You're a thief, Gerhardt!

1938
01:35:02.405 --> 01:35:04.073
Be careful, come on, come on.
Be careful. Come on, stop it.

1939
01:35:04.198 --> 01:35:06.242
-This is stealing!
-Hey, hey, stop it. Come on.

1940
01:35:06.409 --> 01:35:07.451
All right.

1941
01:35:10.538 --> 01:35:12.456
Watch your step. All right.

1942
01:35:20.548 --> 01:35:21.757
RUDY: <i>What about Trudy's money, Joy?</i>

1943
01:35:21.924 --> 01:35:23.926
You have to pay back Trudy's money.

1944
01:35:24.093 --> 01:35:25.636
This is only getting worse.

1945
01:35:25.803 --> 01:35:27.722
I predicted tragedy, Joy.

1946
01:35:28.139 --> 01:35:30.099
You're racking up quite a steep bill.

1947
01:35:30.266 --> 01:35:33.394
We had to fly out here, bail you out.

1948
01:35:33.561 --> 01:35:36.564
RUDY: Plus it cost us an extra
$10,000 for Ray Cagney...

1949
01:35:36.731 --> 01:35:39.108
this California patent attorney,
to get us to this point.

1950
01:35:39.275 --> 01:35:41.777
RAY: We got the state
to decline prosecution.

1951
01:35:41.944 --> 01:35:43.988
They see it's a contract dispute.

1952
01:35:44.155 --> 01:35:47.658
When you paid royalties
to Derek Markham in Texas...

1953
01:35:47.825 --> 01:35:51.871
it put all your parts and molds
under the umbrella of their patent.

1954
01:35:52.788 --> 01:35:55.958
I see you brought all your drawings
and hung them to prove your design.

1955
01:35:56.125 --> 01:35:58.627
But it's impossible to fight it now.

1956
01:35:58.794 --> 01:36:01.255
You were not properly advised.

1957
01:36:02.590 --> 01:36:03.966
Cristy, please!

1958
01:36:04.133 --> 01:36:05.176
Tony, take her to bed.

1959
01:36:05.301 --> 01:36:07.428
I don't wanna go to bed.
I wanna stay here.

1960
01:36:07.595 --> 01:36:08.971
I paid those royalties...

1961
01:36:09.138 --> 01:36:10.181
because you told me to.

1962
01:36:10.306 --> 01:36:12.975
Because your lawyer told me to.

1963
01:36:13.142 --> 01:36:16.937
TRUDY: Our lawyer was mistaken.
This happens sometimes in business.

1964
01:36:17.104 --> 01:36:18.314
It didn't work out for you.

1965
01:36:18.481 --> 01:36:19.482
It happens sometimes.

1966
01:36:19.648 --> 01:36:20.983
Trudy's lawyer is not a patent attorney.

1967
01:36:21.150 --> 01:36:22.485
Which I said!

1968
01:36:22.651 --> 01:36:26.447
And you said I had no business
being Joy's advisor.

1969
01:36:26.489 --> 01:36:28.824
-And now it turns out that I was right!
-This is not helpful, Tony!

1970
01:36:28.866 --> 01:36:30.701
-That's enough, Tony. Please.
-It's enough, now?

1971
01:36:30.826 --> 01:36:33.454
RAY: I'm very sorry.
I wish there was more I could do.

1972
01:36:33.621 --> 01:36:36.707
But when your sister Peggy paid
the unjustified bills...

1973
01:36:36.874 --> 01:36:38.542
that you refused to pay...

1974
01:36:38.709 --> 01:36:40.169
it closed the door on that.

1975
01:36:40.336 --> 01:36:42.046
What about Neil Walker and QVC?

1976
01:36:42.213 --> 01:36:44.715
Wouldn't they pay the expenses
on defending the patent?

1977
01:36:45.508 --> 01:36:46.550
RUDY: Be careful, Joy.

1978
01:36:46.675 --> 01:36:50.304
You could be sued for misrepresentation
and failure to deliver your product.

1979
01:36:50.471 --> 01:36:51.514
That's breach.

1980
01:36:52.389 --> 01:36:55.684
QVC requires that you deliver
a fully patented product.

1981
01:36:55.851 --> 01:36:58.187
RAY: I've been doing this for a long time.

1982
01:36:58.354 --> 01:37:02.358
You're in for a long court process
that will stall your product.

1983
01:37:02.525 --> 01:37:03.984
And you will probably lose.

1984
01:37:04.151 --> 01:37:05.528
I wish I could do more.

1985
01:37:07.196 --> 01:37:08.531
Take care, now.

1986
01:37:08.697 --> 01:37:10.991
Uh, you're gonna have to
accept the facts, Joy.

1987
01:37:11.158 --> 01:37:12.576
I mean, that's...

1988
01:37:13.202 --> 01:37:15.204
You're most of half a million dollars
in debt.

1989
01:37:15.371 --> 01:37:17.206
I don't know how you're gonna pay it.

1990
01:37:17.540 --> 01:37:19.208
We have to declare bankruptcy.

1991
01:37:19.375 --> 01:37:21.752
You're gonna have to declare bankruptcy.

1992
01:37:22.169 --> 01:37:23.337
I have to declare bankruptcy.

1993
01:37:23.504 --> 01:37:24.547
She has to.

1994
01:37:24.672 --> 01:37:26.048
-To try to contain my losses.
-Yeah.

1995
01:37:26.215 --> 01:37:27.383
I have to write it off.

1996
01:37:27.550 --> 01:37:29.510
It just seems so wrong.

1997
01:37:29.677 --> 01:37:31.220
We've worked so hard.

1998
01:37:31.387 --> 01:37:33.430
We've come so far
for us to just give up now.

1999
01:37:33.597 --> 01:37:35.057
It just seems so unfair!

2000
01:37:35.224 --> 01:37:37.726
Business is unfair. That's it.

2001
01:37:37.893 --> 01:37:39.895
It's not working out.
Well, that's what happens.

2002
01:37:40.062 --> 01:37:43.774
That's why people don't go around
making invention every other day.

2003
01:37:43.941 --> 01:37:45.025
Wake up!

2004
01:37:45.067 --> 01:37:46.193
RUDY: It's my fault.

2005
01:37:46.235 --> 01:37:49.321
I gave her the confidence to think she was
more than just an unemployed housewife...

2006
01:37:49.405 --> 01:37:52.032
selling plastic kitchen stuff
to other unemployed housewives...

2007
01:37:52.074 --> 01:37:53.200
on a junk cable channel.

2008
01:37:53.367 --> 01:37:56.078
It's my fault.
It's not your fault, honey.

2009
01:37:56.245 --> 01:37:58.747
It was my mistake to make her think
that she was more than she was.

2010
01:37:59.248 --> 01:38:01.792
She pressured herself into doing something
she shouldn't have done.

2011
01:38:01.917 --> 01:38:03.919
It was wrong of you
to put that pressure on yourself.

2012
01:38:04.086 --> 01:38:06.297
It was wrong of us
to put that pressure on you.

2013
01:38:06.463 --> 01:38:07.923
-(ice cubes rattling)
-I need more vodka.

2014
01:38:08.090 --> 01:38:13.762
It was wrong of us to think that you'd be
an instant business person overnight.

2015
01:38:13.929 --> 01:38:16.432
Of course, this is not who you are.

2016
01:38:17.433 --> 01:38:22.396
It takes a kind of toughness,
a certain acumen...

2017
01:38:22.563 --> 01:38:25.316
that you simply don't have.

2018
01:38:25.983 --> 01:38:27.318
Sign the paper.

2019
01:38:31.906 --> 01:38:34.325
RUDY: You have to sign
these bankruptcy papers, honey.

2020
01:38:34.491 --> 01:38:36.994
The notary's right outside.
Let me get her.

2021
01:38:40.998 --> 01:38:43.125
You're gonna have to move
out of your house immediately.

2022
01:38:44.084 --> 01:38:45.461
You're gonna have to move
into an apartment.

2023
01:38:46.170 --> 01:38:48.297
Maybe you can move into a room
in Trudy's house.

2024
01:38:48.464 --> 01:38:49.632
With the children?

2025
01:38:49.798 --> 01:38:51.592
RUDY: Yeah. You have room.

2026
01:38:52.009 --> 01:38:53.469
She's my daughter. Why not?

2027
01:38:54.803 --> 01:38:56.347
Let's talk about it.

2028
01:38:56.847 --> 01:38:58.349
RUDY: Trudy,
we have to offer her something.

2029
01:38:58.515 --> 01:38:59.642
TRUDY: Again?

2030
01:38:59.683 --> 01:39:00.976
Why me?

2031
01:39:08.525 --> 01:39:10.319
RUDY: Please sign, honey.

2032
01:39:31.382 --> 01:39:32.466
(stamp clicks)

2033
01:39:36.679 --> 01:39:37.721
Thank you.

2034
01:39:41.517 --> 01:39:45.896
Mimi said you were the one born
to help carry the family to success.

2035
01:39:49.483 --> 01:39:52.236
No, Cristy. Mimi was wrong.

2036
01:39:53.696 --> 01:39:55.906
The world does not give you opportunities.

2037
01:39:56.073 --> 01:40:00.869
The world destroys your opportunity
and it breaks your heart.

2038
01:40:01.537 --> 01:40:05.082
I should have listened to my mother
when I was 10 years old.

2039
01:40:05.249 --> 01:40:06.875
I should have spent the rest of my life...

2040
01:40:07.042 --> 01:40:10.045
watching TV and hiding from the world
like my mother.

2041
01:40:11.005 --> 01:40:13.549
So I don't wanna hear
any more about Mimi.

2042
01:40:13.841 --> 01:40:15.217
(sniffles) She was wrong.

2043
01:40:15.384 --> 01:40:18.846
She had her head in the clouds.
And it was full of stupid ideas.

2044
01:40:19.013 --> 01:40:21.181
And it gave me stupid ideas.

2045
01:40:21.390 --> 01:40:22.558
(sobs)

2046
01:40:23.726 --> 01:40:24.727
Like this.

2047
01:40:27.563 --> 01:40:29.732
This stupid, stupid idea!

2048
01:40:29.898 --> 01:40:31.608
-(mop clatters)
-(Joy crying)

2049
01:40:32.693 --> 01:40:35.237
CRISTY: Mommy, don't tear them! No!

2050
01:40:38.699 --> 01:40:39.867
(yells)

2051
01:40:42.953 --> 01:40:44.621
(continues crying)

2052
01:40:56.925 --> 01:40:59.094
(whispers) Cristy, I'm so sorry.

2053
01:40:59.261 --> 01:41:01.305
I'm sorry, Cristy.

2054
01:41:01.472 --> 01:41:03.098
I'm so sorry.

2055
01:41:03.265 --> 01:41:05.642
Please go to bed.
Everybody just go to bed.

2056
01:41:07.102 --> 01:41:08.729
Good night, Mommy.

2057
01:41:08.896 --> 01:41:10.981
JOY: Good night, sweetheart.
Just go to bed.

2058
01:41:13.609 --> 01:41:16.236
RUDY: I'm so sorry I failed you, Joy.
I'm so sorry.

2059
01:41:16.403 --> 01:41:17.946
JOY: Just, just don't.

2060
01:41:19.948 --> 01:41:21.241
(door closes)

2061
01:42:49.621 --> 01:42:51.874
Joy? Joy?

2062
01:42:52.541 --> 01:42:53.917
Joy, where are you?

2063
01:42:55.919 --> 01:42:57.713
Joy, where are you?

2064
01:44:07.366 --> 01:44:08.492
(knocking on door)

2065
01:44:11.370 --> 01:44:12.663
It's open.

2066
01:44:20.462 --> 01:44:21.797
You can leave the door open.

2067
01:44:47.781 --> 01:44:49.741
No one knows I'm here.

2068
01:44:50.784 --> 01:44:52.786
You don't even know who I am.

2069
01:44:52.953 --> 01:44:55.122
I could be Derek Markham

2070
01:44:55.163 --> 01:44:58.458
or I might be someone Derek Markham sent
to handle you.

2071
01:44:58.917 --> 01:45:00.961
You have no case.

2072
01:45:01.461 --> 01:45:05.340
Maybe people think you came to Dallas
in despair to take your own life...

2073
01:45:05.507 --> 01:45:07.426
because you were
in such deep financial trouble

2074
01:45:07.509 --> 01:45:10.429
suddenly from your little venture.

2075
01:45:17.102 --> 01:45:20.397
I made a phone call this morning
to Hong Kong.

2076
01:45:21.064 --> 01:45:23.066
It was 1:00 a.m. in California

2077
01:45:23.150 --> 01:45:26.153
but it was 5:00 p.m.
the following afternoon in Hong Kong.

2078
01:45:26.320 --> 01:45:30.615
I always think it's amazing
how time works like that.

2079
01:45:32.367 --> 01:45:35.495
And I was fortunate enough to get
on the phone with Mr. Christopher...

2080
01:45:35.662 --> 01:45:38.707
who I found to be very friendly,
which was surprising...

2081
01:45:38.874 --> 01:45:42.002
because I really haven't found
the gentlemen in California to be very nice...

2082
01:45:42.169 --> 01:45:44.546
considering we're all
in business together.

2083
01:45:44.713 --> 01:45:48.508
Welcome to the world of business,
I guess.

2084
01:45:49.551 --> 01:45:51.803
I told Mr. Christopher
that the reason that I was calling...

2085
01:45:51.970 --> 01:45:56.016
was to discuss the differences
in the designs of our products.

2086
01:45:56.641 --> 01:46:01.021
But I quickly learned that
Mr. Christopher has no idea...

2087
01:46:01.188 --> 01:46:04.483
if his Hong Kong patent
for a self-wringing mop

2088
01:46:04.566 --> 01:46:07.319
is worth anything or if it even works.

2089
01:46:07.944 --> 01:46:13.033
Because they have not made
or sold a single mop.

2090
01:46:13.283 --> 01:46:16.995
Unlike us, who have sold over 200,000.

2091
01:46:18.121 --> 01:46:22.918
And I've paid you over $50,000
in advanced royalties...

2092
01:46:23.085 --> 01:46:25.045
on behalf of Mr. Christopher.

2093
01:46:25.587 --> 01:46:30.467
Blood money from my family
and my second mortgage.

2094
01:46:31.760 --> 01:46:36.014
Turns out Mr. Christopher doesn't know
anything about those royalties.

2095
01:46:36.264 --> 01:46:37.724
So it seems...

2096
01:46:38.892 --> 01:46:42.479
we have a case of fraud and embezzlement.

2097
01:46:45.524 --> 01:46:48.735
And, as if that weren't bad enough...

2098
01:46:49.611 --> 01:46:51.738
I also discovered in the paperwork

2099
01:46:51.822 --> 01:46:55.117
that our mops actually
don't bear any similarities.

2100
01:46:55.283 --> 01:46:58.412
So I never did owe you
any royalties for your patent.

2101
01:46:59.454 --> 01:47:01.415
That's another case of fraud.

2102
01:47:02.082 --> 01:47:07.963
My lawyers really could go after you,
but I told them, "Give me a day."

2103
01:47:08.130 --> 01:47:14.094
To see if maybe
you might've made a mistake...

2104
01:47:15.929 --> 01:47:18.849
that you would correct,
given the chance.

2105
01:47:34.281 --> 01:47:37.242
We'll pay you back all the royalties
you paid us.

2106
01:47:41.455 --> 01:47:46.960
(stammering) I'll give you $20,000
on top of paying you back the 50.

2107
01:47:58.889 --> 01:48:00.140
Okay.

2108
01:48:01.850 --> 01:48:05.562
I'll give you $50,000
on top of paying you back the 50.

2109
01:48:17.657 --> 01:48:19.242
Plus interest.

2110
01:48:24.706 --> 01:48:26.708
I want all of my molds back.

2111
01:48:27.375 --> 01:48:29.669
I want you to sign this piece of paper...

2112
01:48:30.712 --> 01:48:33.965
saying that you have
no rights, financially.

2113
01:48:35.008 --> 01:48:38.470
I'm just gonna add...
I said the 50...

2114
01:48:40.597 --> 01:48:42.557
plus the 50...

2115
01:48:44.351 --> 01:48:47.020
plus the interest.

2116
01:48:47.187 --> 01:48:51.274
So I just want you to initial
next to those two numbers as well.

2117
01:48:57.322 --> 01:48:58.865
So just sign there.

2118
01:49:06.831 --> 01:49:09.376
MIMI: <i>She put up with just about anything.</i>

2119
01:49:10.377 --> 01:49:12.796
<i>Until when she had to</i>
<i>bring the hammer down...</i>

2120
01:49:14.381 --> 01:49:16.049
<i>she brought the hammer down.</i>

2121
01:49:18.385 --> 01:49:21.012
<i>She couldn't know what was to come.</i>

2122
01:49:21.930 --> 01:49:25.976
<i>That she'd go on to make</i>
<i>another 100 record-setting patents.</i>

2123
01:49:26.935 --> 01:49:30.480
<i>Skinny velvet hangers</i>
<i>make neater closets.</i>

2124
01:49:30.647 --> 01:49:32.983
<i>That's a big deal to a lot of people.</i>

2125
01:49:34.150 --> 01:49:36.611
<i>I mean, who thinks of things like that?</i>

2126
01:49:37.779 --> 01:49:39.030
<i>Joy did.</i>

2127
01:49:43.326 --> 01:49:48.540
<i>She didn't know any of this would happen</i>
<i>as she walked down the street that day.</i>

2128
01:49:49.249 --> 01:49:50.250
MAN: Yes, sir.

2129
01:49:50.333 --> 01:49:53.253
Tonight's the night for Ol' Saint Nick
to make his yearly visit

2130
01:49:53.420 --> 01:49:55.380
to all the folks all over the world.

2131
01:49:55.547 --> 01:49:59.050
There's fun and expectation
in every house across the land.

2132
01:49:59.217 --> 01:50:03.305
And speaking of houses, what do you say
we take a little look-in on a typical one?

2133
01:50:03.388 --> 01:50:05.307
(music box playing
"Winter Wonderland")

2134
01:50:06.308 --> 01:50:11.730
Now I'll admit that what you see right now
is just a small piece of the front of a house,

2135
01:50:11.896 --> 01:50:15.692
but all you grownups and kids alike,
this is the time for Santa's magic.

2136
01:50:15.859 --> 01:50:19.029
So I think we can make it
become a real house.

2137
01:50:19.904 --> 01:50:21.448
Even a house with love in it.

2138
01:50:21.531 --> 01:50:24.618
Mr. Santa Claus, can we have
a little snow, please?

2139
01:50:26.661 --> 01:50:28.622
Thank you. That's fine.

2140
01:50:28.872 --> 01:50:32.959
Now, Santa, let me see what it
really looks like inside this house.

2141
01:50:33.168 --> 01:50:35.962
("A House With Love In It" playing)

2142
01:50:44.471 --> 01:50:45.722
See what I mean?

2143
01:50:46.931 --> 01:50:49.643
♪ A house with love in it ♪

2144
01:50:51.686 --> 01:50:54.230
♪ Is rich indeed ♪

2145
01:50:55.315 --> 01:50:58.860
♪ Although there are a thousand things ♪

2146
01:50:59.611 --> 01:51:01.863
♪ That house may need ♪

2147
01:51:02.322 --> 01:51:06.826
MIMI: <i>She couldn't know that one day</i>
<i>she would move into a big beautiful home.</i>

2148
01:51:09.371 --> 01:51:11.623
<i>Her mother was happy.</i>

2149
01:51:12.415 --> 01:51:16.670
<i>She remained close to her,</i>
<i>and with the rest of her family...</i>

2150
01:51:16.836 --> 01:51:19.547
<i>which was, as always, complicated.</i>

2151
01:51:21.716 --> 01:51:26.888
<i>She would pay for products</i>
<i>made by Rudy, Trudy, and Peggy.</i>

2152
01:51:27.097 --> 01:51:29.182
<i>Even when they failed.</i>

2153
01:51:29.849 --> 01:51:34.562
<i>Even when they wrongly sued</i>
<i>for ownership of her company.</i>

2154
01:51:35.438 --> 01:51:36.981
<i>As Rudy got older,</i>

2155
